      • handleIntentWithGcm

        protected abstract void handleIntentWithGcm(com.google.android.gms.gcm.GoogleCloudMessaging gcm,
                                            Intent intent)
        Subclasses should implement this in order to handle incoming intents. Called by onHandleIntent(), which handles some boilerplate code. This is where you will parse the content of incoming Intents and send the results as Notifications.
        Parameters:
        gcm - Instance of GoogleCloudMessaging instance to use
        intent - Incoming intent to handle
